description: Nestled in the heart of the High Sierras at an elevation of 4,300 feet, Feather River Park Resort's nine-hole golf course offers stunning views of meadows, canyons, and dozens of lakes that are scattered throughout the rustic countryside of the Mohawk Valley. Sand and grass bunkers complement the strategic mounding across the gently rolling landscape of the course, making ball placement a top priority in scoring well. This wooded golf course has pine trees lining its fairways and a water hazard coming into play. For avid golfers, Feather River Park Resort provides a challenging practice round for the two championship 18-hole courses that are nearby.

Sun Lakes Country Club Executive Course

description: The golf course at the Cottonwood Country Club is a traditional layout on a natural desert terrain. There is some desert landscaping that comes into play along the sides of the fairway. Water hazards and sand bunkers come into play on a few holes. The course's finishing hole is its signature; it is a par-4 hole that calls for an approach shot over a lake in order to reach the green. With four sets of tees, the course appeals to any skill level of golfer. Cottonwood Country Club also offers a driving range, chipping area, and putting green for its golfers.
